    <h1 id="title">John Michuki</h1>
    <p>The minister who tamed Kenya's matatu industry</p>

    <div id="img-div">
     <img id="image" src="images/Michuki.jpg" alt="John Michuki">
      <p id="img-caption">
        John Michuki addressing the press during his time as a Cabinet Minister
        in Kenya.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p id="tribute-info">Here's a timeline of John Michuki's life:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>1932 - Born in Muguru village, Iyego Location, Kangema Division, Murang'a District</li>
      <li>1943 - Drops out of school due to financial problems and moves to Nairobi to work in tailoring</li>
      <li>1945 - Passes his Kenya African Primary Education (KAPE) exam at Kiangunyi Primary School</li>
      <li>1947 - Joins Nyeri High School, later moving to Mang'u High School for his A-Levels, where he meets lifelong friend Mwai Kibaki</li>
      <li>1957 - Begins his civil service career as a clerk in the Provincial Administration</li>
      <li>1961 - Graduates from Worcester College, Oxford, with a degree in Economics, Finance and Public Administration</li>
      <li>1961 - Returns to Kenya and becomes the first African District Commissioner</li>
      <li>1970s-1990s - Serves as Permanent Secretary in the Finance Ministry and Chairman of the Kenya Commercial Bank</li>
      <li>2002 - Appointed Cabinet Minister under President Mwai Kibaki</li>
      <li>2004 - Introduces the "Michuki Rules" as Minister of Transport, drastically reducing road accidents and restoring order to the matatu industry</li>
      <li>2007-2008 - Serves as Minister for Internal Security during the post-election violence period</li>
      <li>2008 - Becomes Minister for Environment and Natural Resources</li>
      <li>2012 - Dies at the age of 79</li>
    </ul>

    <p id="tribute-info">
      "When you rattle a snake, you must be prepared to be bitten."<br>
      -- John Michuki
    </p>

    <p>
      If you have time, you should read more about this incredible leader on his
      <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_Michuki" target="_blank">Wikipedia entry</a>.
    </p>

